Biden: Putin cannot stay in power. White House: Biden meant that Putin should not be allowed to use force against neighbors or the region. He wasn't referring to Putin's power in Russia or regime change. Biden: Putin needs to be removed from power, regime change in Russia is needed. White House: Biden was referring to the need to deprive Putin of the ability to negatively influence neighboring countries. We are talking about changing the regime of Russia's self-isolation. Biden: We need to take away political power from Putin, we need to change the political regime in Russia. White House: Biden meant the democratic development of Russia and the change of the political regime in a democratic way.